<title>BELGIUM: Kredietbank lowers Artwork to &quot;neutral+&quot;.</title>
<headline>Kredietbank lowers Artwork to &quot;neutral+&quot;.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-07-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Belgian bank Kredietbank said in an investor note dated July 3 it lowered its rating on shares in Belgian, Easdaq-listed, printing software maker Artwork Systems to &quot;neutral plus&quot; from &quot;undervalued&quot; because 1997 earnings were not likely to live up to expectations.</p>
<p>&quot;We estimate net earnings per share will grow in 1997 by 25 percent rather than the 47 percent we had estimated initially,&quot; KB said in its Infor-Placements/Beleggingsberichten magazine.</p>
<p>&quot;With a price/earnings ratio of 20.8 and expected annual profit growth of 30 percent the share is attractive but not particulary cheap,&quot; it added.</p>
<p>-- Nick Antonovics, Brussels Newsroom +32 2 287 6817, Fax +32 2 230 7710</p>
